\toc1 The Letter from Jude
\mt1 The letter that Jude wrote
\mt2 (The book in the Holy Bible called \bk Jude\bk*)
\imt1 About this letter
\ip Jude wrote this letter about 2,000 years ago, about 30 years after Jesus went back to heaven, and now it is in the Holy Bible.
\ip At that time, the name \em Jude\em* and the name \em Judas\em* were 2 ways of saying the same name. The man that wrote this letter was probably Jesus’s brother Judas (see Mark 6:2-3), but he might have been one of Jesus’s special workers called Judas (see John 14:22; Acts 1:13).
\ip Jude wrote this letter to tell the Christians about some people that reckoned they were saying God’s words, but they were lying. Jude told the Christians to be very careful of them, and to keep on living God’s way.
\ip These words that Jude wrote have very important messages for all of us Christians.
\cl Chapter
\c 1
\p 
\v 1 \w This|strong="G3588"\w* letter \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* me, \w Jude|strong="G2455"\w*. \w I|strong="G2532"\w* work \w for|strong="G1161"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w*’m \w a|strong="G2532"\w* brother \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w James|strong="G2385"\w*. \w I|strong="G2532"\w*’m writing \w this|strong="G3588"\w* letter \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G1722"\w* \w people|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* loves. \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w father|strong="G3962"\w*. \w He|strong="G2532"\w* picked \w you|strong="G1722"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w his|strong="G1722"\w* \w people|strong="G3588"\w*. \w He|strong="G2532"\w* helps \w you|strong="G1722"\w* stay \w strong|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G1161"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*, \w until|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w comes|strong="G2532"\w* back.\x * \xo 1:1 \xt Matthew 13:55; Mark 6:3\x*
\p 
